snippet.textDisplay:
other important things people always get wrong
-- don't put a cold ass steak into a pan. it fucks so many things up.
-- don't use shitty oil like vegetable, crisco, canola blends, or overly fancy crap like extra virgin.

-- don't burn / smoke the oil. you'll know you fucked up when the pan / oil smells bitter and unappetizing
-- don't use a thin ass flimsy weightless pan. it doesn't get hot enough, and it can't stay hot
-- if there isn't a loud, consistent sizzle the whole time you're searing the steak, you fucked up
-- if most of the surface area of the steak is gray instead of brown, you fucked up
-- if most of the inside of the steak is gray, you fucked up
-- don't eat it if you fucked up

snippet.textDisplay: The perfect steak is the way you like it. Mine is cooked on a grill using Mesquite wood, and having several sauces to dip it in. Soy sauce, and black pepper. Mayo, horseradish, and ketchup! Sour cream, and McCormick's roasted garlic and herb! Honey, mustard, and hot sauce. Then there is the steak itself. I like mine still kicking, while my wife likes what I would call shoe leather. When it comet to cooking; What I like; you may hate.
